INSERT INTO `phpbb_privmsgs_text` VALUES (509,'16a87e39e2','Hello Pete,\r\n\r\nThank you so much for your swift responce. I would absolutely love to invite the Palmetto State Brewer\'s club to the Columbia Music Festival Association\'s 24th annual Pub Night. I was thinking that this event would be right up your ally, and in the future I would love to organize a local brewing competition at the Pub Night, maybe with a nice people\'s choice award, who knows?\r\n\r\nAt any rate I am going to post our Press Release to you at the very least, I hope you will take a look at it and let me know if this is an event you are willing to support and tell your membership about. I hope to see you on the 4th at a fun-filled evenning of food and drink!\r\n\r\nPress Release:\r\n\r\nCOLUMBIA MUSIC FESTIVAL ASSOCIATION\r\n914 PULASKI STREET\r\nCOLUMBIA, SOUTH CAROLINA 29201\r\n803.771.6303 * FAX 803.771.2625\r\n\r\nNEWS RELEASE\r\n\r\n\r\nFOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE;\r\n\r\nColumbia, SC - Come drink and be merry as The Columbia Music Festival Association hosts the 24th annual Ye Olde Pub Night on February 4th, 7:30 PM, at the CMFA ArtSpace, 914 Pulaski Street.\r\n\r\nThis annual benefit features traditional English Pub foods with ales, beers,\r\n\r\ndomestic wines and a regulation English Darts Tournament coordinated by dartsmaster, Joe Hodson.\r\n\r\nWith hundreds of dollars worth of door prizes and drawing prizes contributed by many of the areas leading merchants and hearty food provided by Southern Way Catering, this event has become one of the \"hottest tickets\" of the benefit season.\r\n\r\nLong-time Columbia, SC television personality Joe Pinner will be returning to emcee the event.\r\n\r\nEach season the Pub Night benefit provides the Columbia Music Festival\r\n\r\nAssociation (CMFA) with additional supplemental funding to help fulfill its\r\n\r\nmission as an arts resource for the community.  Pub Night brings darts \r\n\r\nenthusiasts, party goers, and others together for a casual evening of revelry, merriment, and supporting The arts.  CMFA President and chair of the Pub Night event, Cydney Berry said, \"Pub Night brings out such an eclectic and diverse group from all over the State, that it takes the \'arts\' off the pedestal and makes everyone aware not only of the importance of supporting the arts, but more importantly that the arts are FUN for everyone.\"\r\n\r\n	 Charlie Sterne, Co-Chair of Pub Night, has put together a group of young \r\n\r\n	volunteers who transform the CMFA ArtSpace into an inviting\r\n\r\nneighborhood Pub.  Like the pubs which dot the English Countryside, \r\n\r\nPub Night provides a comfortable, friendly atmosphere whether one \r\n\r\nattends alone or with a group.  While the darts tournament\r\n\r\nsets the tone for the evening, the drawings, food and spirits keep the\r\n\r\nnight lively and entertaining for everyone. \r\n\r\nTickets for Pub Night are available at the CMFA ArtSpace, 914 Pulaski St.\r\n\r\nor by calling the CMFA at 771.6303.  Tickets are $20 in advance and $25\r\n\r\nat the door.\r\n\r\nFor further information contact the CMFA at 771.6303.\r\n\r\n                                                  # # #\r\n\r\n \r\n	Contact:  Dan Fenner - 771-6303');
INSERT INTO `phpbb_privmsgs_text` VALUES (510,'f245e6dd02','Daniel -\r\n\r\nI have posted your press release to the public part of the forum so that all members and guests can see.  Thanks for taking the time to extend this invitation via PM with a \'heads-up\' the other day.  It looks like a fun event and I think at this late date I can only promise to post and hope everyone gets a chance to read.  The forum is a new thing for the club and although most members have signed in there are some hold-outs.  :wink: \r\n\r\nPer your message it would be nice to have some entries for a fun-competition.  As it takes 1-2 months (at least) to make a beer I\'m afraid it won\'t work out this year!  Also, next time I will present the information to the club at our monthly meeting (2nd Mondays).  \r\n\r\nAgain, thanks for the invitation and I hope we can deliver a few members to your event.\r\n\r\n- Pete\r\n\r\n :cheers:');
