INSERT INTO `phpbb_privmsgs_text` VALUES (3046,'c588e04fb4','Hey Brian, I am a fellow PSBer recently moved back home to Mullins, SC.  We are not that far from each other, but I am in an area that has next to nothing of a sort for brewing supplies and CO2.  I was wondering if you had any suggestions for me as to where I may find some supplies and most importantly (at this point) CO2 because I am [u:c588e04fb4][b:c588e04fb4]OUT[/b:c588e04fb4][/u:c588e04fb4].  I have been getting my CO2 from National Welders in Florence, but they are unappealing to my schedule (no weekends) and I think they were shanking me on my CO2.  It seems that when I place my primary regulator on the tank it gets no higher than 500 psi and I am paying $20 for 15# CO2 that I am not getting.  I have heard of a place that might would fill me up or exchange somewhere near the beach, but just not sure if there was any truth to it.  If you could please let me know your ideas on my CO2 problem and as to where I may find some supplies in the area; I am just tired of paying shipping charges.  Thanks in advance.\r\n\r\n\r\nScott Hasty');
