INSERT INTO `phpbb_privmsgs_text` VALUES (4579,'537bd046d8','I\'m getting more comfortable with where the RIS is at.  I almost dropped in the oak this weekend.  I think I\'ll do it pretty soon.  Clearly the gravity is quite stable.  Mine\'s holding at 1.038 for 3 weeks now.  I agree with MAZ that carbonation will take away some of the maltiness from the palate and we can always do a dry stout.  I\'m thinking about doing that for St. Pat\'s.  One of the best beers I brewed was an all extract dry stout from Bet-Mar\'s can collection.  No grain, just add water and yeast.\r\n\r\nI was looking at your stupid beer recipe yesterday thinking I would like to make that for the summer.  Similarly, I have the braggot cold conditioning in the cooler Pete gave me.  It\'s holding at between 50-54 degrees.  I\'ll need to leave it there for 2 months.  Tasted great the last time I tested it.\r\n\r\nI\'ve been reading the Ale Trail book I won at the open.  I\'ll give it to you when I\'m done.  It\'s very fun.  I just finished the chapter on IPA\'s.  Great stuff.  Alcohol and hops as a preservative!\r\n\r\nHave you started the yeast for the Sami?  We need to get working on that bad boy pretty soon.  Marlene cleared out a piece of furniture from my brew room already.');
