INSERT INTO `phpbb_privmsgs_text` VALUES (3456,'af219135a3','Setting aside everything else I disagree with the basis of your argument that it is the governments responsibility to take care of all of its citizens needs.  The form of government you describe is at least socialist.  America is a Republic.  Here the free markets rule and competition and competitive advantages promote the economy.  This is what has made America the most economically powerful and stable nation in history.  Socialism  undermines that.\r\n\r\nIll admit my perfect world is based on Objectivism.  As I mentioned in my post I have throughout my life spent a money out of pocket on health care.  I believe no one is responsible for me but me and therefore it is inconsistent (even incomprehensible) to consider taking money away from any other America citizen to pay for my medical needs; whatever the expense.  If I cannot afford insurance or care then I would be compelled to seek help from family or private charitable organizations.  Additionally, I have and will negotiate with medical providers.  Often hospital bills will be reduced by simply talking to the business office and setting up payment plans.\r\n\r\nAs an example of the abuse of our medical system by people that do not want to accept responsibility for themselves I offer the following.  About 2.5 years ago my next door neighbor was diagnosed with a heart problem.  He was about 32 years old and married with 3 kids.  He told me he did not have insurance because he was self employed and could not afford it.  I genuinely felt badly him and his family.  His house was ultimately foreclosed on about a year ago.\r\n\r\nHowever, before he moved and AFTER his diagnosis he bought a Corvette, two Harley Davidsons and his wife purchased a brand new SUV.  Everything was a cash purchase except the SUV.  Many weekends he traveled with his daughters softball team at, what he said, was a considerable expense.  A few months after his foreclosure I saw one of his daughters and asked about him.  She exclaimed, Hes doing great!  He just got a new Harley!\r\n\r\nThis is a man who had a number of insurance options available to him and his family.  This is a man who had the ability to pay for his healthcare out of his pocket.  This is a man who made the choice to spend his money on lifes luxuries while neglecting his and his familys healthcare needs.\r\n\r\nIm sorry but he is not unique.  I do not want to have money taken from me to help pay for someone so irresponsible.  I do not mind helping the truly needy but I will only do that through private charitable organizations or on a personal basis.  People should be accountable for their own decisions and socialized medicine removes that accountably.\r\n\r\nI hope you can see my point on this issue.');
