INSERT INTO `phpbb_privmsgs_text` VALUES (2361,'6898ea8da5','Harold, I have been researching onions again for the experimental onion beer.  It is really neat stuff actually.  I am leaning toward dry hopping persae with onions to not destroy the overall beer.  With that being said, I have found through research that soaking chopped onions in acetic acid help ward off the sulfuric acid that would be produced through the cutting process.  My question is how much acetic acid does it take to create negative affects to the environment inside the fermenter and the beer?  Also at that stage in fermenting is it possible that the acidity of the soaked onion would stop ferementation?  Do you think it would be better to wait and add at say tertiary fermentation?  Keep in mind I am not trying overpower the beer, just lend subtle hints to give the simple aroma and slight flavor of onion.  Any advice would be greatly appreciated.\r\n\r\nThanks\r\nScott Hasty');
