INSERT INTO `phpbb_privmsgs_text` VALUES (4776,'2d03de867b','Meeting Agenda\r\nEvent Planning\r\nWort Chillers\r\nTasting\r\n\r\nFrom The President\r\nFebruaryahhhlove is in the airthe month of cupid and Valentines Day.  Dont forget to show your sweetie just how important they are to you.  You KNOW what they want.  What better way show your love than to present them with a cool, frothy mug of home brew that you have so painstakingly and delicately craftedjust for them.  Nothing else says I love you like a home brew, so go ahead, spoil your sweetheart, be a hero.\r\n\r\nPrices for brewing ingredients are creeping up because of the recent hop and grain crises.  BUT, they are still affordable and you CAN find hops at your local home brew shop.  You might not find the hops you are used to, but you can substitute.    Go ahead, experiment, and brew something different!  \r\nIf you have experience with substitutes for hops in beer, or know someone that does, please contact Chris, our Education Guru.\r\n\r\nThe first CBoY competition of 2008, the Shamrock Open in Raleigh, is scheduled for March 15. Plans are being developed to have entries from our club amassed and passed on to get to the competition site.  Registration for the competition is now open and can be made on line. Get those entries ready and registered. Lets maintain the firkin trophy two years in a row.  Go PSB!    \r\n\r\nThank you Gadget Man Jim Griggers for hosting Januarys remarkably informative and enjoyable brew session.  These monthly brew sessions are a great format to socialize, sample assorted beers, and to share brewing techniques with fellow club members.  Sign up to host and come join in on the fun.\r\n\r\nSeveral club events are in the works for this year.  Included are club sponsored cigar and pint nights, brewery tours, beer/food pairing dinner, Big Brew Day, and of course the semi-annual club party scheduled for April 12.  WHAT A CLUB!\r\n\r\nIll see you at Zorbas on Monday the 11th, 6:00 dinner, 7:00 meeting.  Be sure to bring homebrew to share and to show off.\r\n\r\nAnd dont forget, this Valentines Day say it with home brew.\r\n\r\nCarl Foster/ Prez');
