INSERT INTO `phpbb_privmsgs_text` VALUES (4139,'476c72c917','Hey Brian,\r\nI believe I saw your postings a while back regarding fridges and schematics and things...correct??\r\nAnyway, I have an old Gibson that I have made into a kegerator and I am wondering if I could easily put an icemaker in it to make ice for brewdays and so forth...  It says it is icemaker ready inside the freezer, can I just buy an icemaker??  would any brand work??  Any advice is much appreciated.  Sorry, I don\'t have model numbers and all at this point, but I can look if necessary.  I can also take pics, whatever...\r\n-Phil');
INSERT INTO `phpbb_privmsgs_text` VALUES (4140,'8d7b36fc2d','Hi Phil, Correct! You should be able to add an Ice maker to your fridge. It is possible that there is an OEM part (original equip part) if not there are several universal Ice makes for domestic refrigerators. The best place to start is a local Air conditioning and refrigeration supply house. I use Johnstone supply for most Items but you have several choices. http://www.johnstonesupply.com/corp/Default.aspx  There is a store locator on this site. Installing a ice maker is simple. You Install a water valve  and water source and the ice maker is installed in the freezer area with a couple screws. If your fridge says Ice maker ready the you have a plug in the freezer for the freezer module. If you go to a supply house they will usually be helpful and tell you what and how. I hope this helps. Let me know if I can help in the future. Prost!');
